text: Hello, I am new to Hyperledger/Blockchain, but would like to understand how is the data accessible/readable in use case of Supply Chain Auditing? Are there already some existing standards about how transactions (and their contents and parties) are identified in such case? If you get handle to one of such transaction, can you then easily find out all the transactions made by same seller and buyer, contents of the transactions and price paid?
I would assume that most of the data doesn’t mean you anything without the context, if it’s just ID, and you do not know where do they point to?
